description: For sale: $550,000. This home will most likely be one of the most immaculate, well cared for homes you will have ever stepped foot in. 153' of sandy beach on Jay Gould, part of the Pokegama Lake Chain. Yellow hardwood birch carry you throughout the main floor. The kitchen embraces black marble countertops and a lakeview. Large 24 x26 detached garage for all the toys the lake lifestyle' encounters. This home has natural gas, public water system and is extremely close to Grand Rapids. Extremely fair taxes.

description: For sale: $239,900. Be sure to view the virtual tour of this spacious, meticulously maintained Cohasset home. Situated on a quiet street with 3/4 acres of beautifully landscaped grounds, towering pines, bountiful perennials and fruit trees, you're just 2 minutes from Portage Park and access to Jay Gould and Pokegama Lakes. Tioga Beach and the new bike trail complex are only 5 minutes away. Enjoy meals in the open concept kitchen and dining area with tons of counter-space. The living room with a Vermont Castings gas fireplace is just as spacious and inviting. There are bathrooms on each level, making the large family room in the basement a great place for movie nights and kids sleep-overs. There's plenty of storage space in the lower-level pantry, utility room and laundry closet, not to mention the shed connected to the home by a convenient breezeway. And the sauna - WOW! There's no better way to end a night in the Northwoods than a relaxing session in a cedar-lined sauna. Check this one out today!
